# Regression Diagnostics

This project evaluates the assumptions of a linear regression model using diagnostic techniques in R. 
The analysis explores the relationship between mushroom abundance and soil measurements while identifying influential observations that may affect model performance.

## Methods
- Linear regression
- Residual diagnostics
- Cook's distance
- Standardized residual analysis
- Log-transformation modeling

## Files
- `regression_diagnostics.R` – R script containing the analysis
- `ex1111.csv` – dataset used in the model

## Tools
- R
- ggplot2
